## Implementation Plan

### Problem
Sentry 26.2.0 release failed because the CHANGELOG body exceeded GitHub's
125,000-character release body limit, causing a 422 error at
github.repos.createRelease().

### Root Cause
The changelog body extracted from CHANGELOG.md (via findChangeset â†’
extractChangeset) was passed directly to the GitHub API with no size check.
The Changeset object was spread into the API request parameters.

### Solution

#### 1. src/utils/changelog.ts
- Extend Changeset interface with optional startLine/endLine (1-indexed)
- Add getLineNumber() helper converting character positions to line numbers
- Modify extractChangeset() to compute line numbers from ChangesetLoc

#### 2. src/targets/github.ts
- Add GITHUB_RELEASE_BODY_MAX = 125,000 constant
- Add buildChangelogPermalink() to construct a permalink:
  https://github.com/{owner}/{repo}/blob/{sha}/{changelog}#L{start}-L{end}
- Add truncateBody() to cut at last newline boundary before the limit and
  append a footer with the permalink
- Refactor createDraftRelease() to explicitly pass name and body (not spread)
  so startLine/endLine do not leak into the API request

#### 3. Tests
- changelog-file-ops.test.ts: 3 tests for startLine/endLine accuracy
  (first section, middle section, setext headings)
- github.test.ts: 5 tests for createDraftRelease truncation behavior
  (short body passthrough, empty body, truncation with permalink,
  line boundary truncation, no line fragment when absent, no extra fields)

### Design Decisions
- Optional fields on Changeset for backward compatibility
- Truncation at line boundaries to avoid cutting markdown mid-line
- Permalink with commit SHA so the link survives future CHANGELOG edits
- Truncation in createDraftRelease since it owns the API call and has access
  to revision and githubConfig
